Project Codex — Core Rules
Project Identity

Name: Project Codex — a personal "Life OS" dashboard
Purpose: Daily Briefing + Kanban Task Manager + Canvas Workspace + Interstitial Diary + AI Planning
Single user, self-hosted on shared PHP hosting + SQLite

Stack at a Glance

Backend: PHP 8.2+, PDO/SQLite, no framework
Frontend: React 18, Vite, TypeScript (strict), Tailwind CSS v3
State: TanStack Query v5 (server state) + Zustand v5 (UI state)
Native: Capacitor v6 (mobile) + Tauri v2 (desktop)
AI: Anthropic API (claude-sonnet-4-20250514)

Universal Naming Conventions

Database columns and PHP variables: snake_case
TypeScript types, interfaces, React components: PascalCase
TypeScript variables, functions, hooks: camelCase
API route segments: kebab-case (/api/diary-logs, not /api/diary_logs)
File names — PHP: PascalCase.php; TS/TSX: PascalCase.tsx for components, camelCase.ts for utils/hooks
CSS classes: Tailwind utility classes only — no custom CSS classes except in tailwind.config.ts theme extension

Timestamps

All timestamps stored as Unix integers (seconds) in SQLite
PHP: use time() for current timestamp; never date() for storage
TypeScript: type alias UnixTimestamp = number; convert to Date only for display
All display formatting uses date-fns — never new Date().toLocaleString()

Soft Deletes

Goals, Projects, Tasks, Notes, DiaryLogs: never hard delete
Set deleted_at = unixepoch() instead
Every query MUST include WHERE deleted_at IS NULL unless explicitly fetching archived/trash items
PHP repositories expose a restore(int $id) method that sets deleted_at = NULL

Error Handling

PHP: all exceptions caught at the front controller; return ApiError JSON envelope; never expose stack traces
TypeScript: all API calls check response.success before accessing .data
No console.log in committed code — use console.error only for genuine errors
User-facing errors shown via the toast system (uiStore.addToast()), never alert()

Security

API protected by X-Codex-Key header middleware on every non-public endpoint
API key stored in backend .env, never in frontend source or git
Frontend reads API key from VITE_API_KEY env var (Vite strips it at build time for native targets)
SQLite file location: backend/database/codex.sqlite — outside public/ webroot
All PDO queries use prepared statements — no string interpolation in SQL ever
OAuth tokens stored in integration_tokens table — never in localStorage or cookies

Git Hygiene

Never commit .env, *.sqlite, *.sqlite-wal, *.sqlite-shm, node_modules/, vendor/
.cursorrules and .cursor/ ARE committed — they are project configuration
